  60433 Frankfurt am Main
  Germany  
  Phone: +49 (69) 5488130
  Fax:   +49 (69) 5481845

- AmyNews doesn't cover games but we want to recommend one of the best
  Amiga games ever made, Colonization. It's ESC and AGA compatible and
  use Amiga intuition. It musltitasks beautifuly and you can run it on
  your workbench too. Colonization is very playable. The sound tracks
  are just awesome. This is a must have game. Order it now and don't
  forget to mention in the registration card that you have bought the
  Amiga version.

  Colonization can be bought in USA from:

  Phone: 01144-1227-764204 (Post Haste)
  Phone: 01144-171-608-0624 (DataGem)

- The German company Prodev has just released a a new and much improved 
  version of their intuition emulator ProBench version 2 for Merlin Graphic
  Board. Hardware update for Merlin board is available through Prodev too.
  The hardware update, solves some problems with other ZorroIII cards, and
  V2 of ProBench and make Merlin to one of the fastest 32bit boards 
  available. The digitizer module for Merlin, Xcalibur is now available for
  sale from ProDev and it has new software. It even has RGB inputs which is
  good for highend users.
  The 24 bit paint program XiPaint is also available from ProDev.

  ProDev - Fa. Hans Raaf
  Eichendorffstr. 9
  53859 Niederkassel
  Germany
  Phone/FAX: +49 2208 73988

- Jesse McClusky is currently developing an all new browser called Weblink
  for the Amiga. Weblink has inbyggd html editor and ssupports HTML 1,2,3,
  NHTML, VRML and Java.
  An overview of Weblink is at http://www.phone.net/~mwm/weblink/overview

- Utilities Unlimited International, inventer of the Amiga Emplant has
  just released version 2.1 of e586DX IBM PC module for the Emplant.
  This new version features:
  
  - Many improvements to compatibility area, Printing enabled (supports
    the parrallel printer port as LPT1) etc
  - MemMaker bug fixed, faster protected mode code etc
  - Hard drive partition limits are really fixed
  - Hard drive partitions are now appeared as a normal AmigaDOS partition
  - software can now be run in 386 Mode. (Windows without the /s)
  - All MMU problems are fixed now (MMU and protected mode are separated 
    now. As a result, games like Doom, Dark Forces, Wolf3d, etc will run
    faster than before
  - 86 memory manager works now without any problems
  - Stack overflow problem that occured on some machines are fixed now
  - New ANSI driver
  - New empdisc.device
  - Parallel port (printer) support
  - uuibios library (to help with CDRom usage)
  - New empcdrom.sys device

  The e586DX v2.1 software in now available on Utilities Unlimited BBS.

  Utilities Unlimited, Inc.
  1641 McCulloch Blvd. Suite #25-124
  Lake Havasu City, AZ  86403
  USA
  Phone: (602) 680-9004
  Phone: (602) 453-6407 
  Fax:   (602) 453-9767 BBS
  BBS:   (602) 453-3909
