- The very lon awaited BlitzGUIGen version 1.5 is now released. BlitzGUIGen
  allows users of Blitz Basic 2 version 1.9 to create Graphical User 
  Interfaces with GadToolsBox v2.0, and convert them into Blitz source.
  The registred version of BlitzGUIGen features:

  - Convertion of custom screens
  - Convertion of custom palettes
  - Supports all gadtools gadgets
  - Supports menu lists
  - Supports bevelboxes (recessed,normal and dropbox)
  - Supports Intuitext
  - Supports font selection in source for text and gadgets
  - Supports crunched .gui files
  - Direct loading of Blitz2 editor from BlitzGUIGen
  - Ability to create .xtra files to accompany source
  - Personalised Key File registration
  - Ability to switch of parts of source (to create includes)
  - Ability to override gui settings
  - Uses ASL or Reqtools requesters
  - Creates 'Main Event Handler' loops for you with meaningful gadget labels

  The unregistred and freely distributable version is available in AmiNet.

  Creative Software (Simon Archer)
  15 Nicoll Court
  Sydney Road
  Muswell Hill
  London N10 2RW
  England

  EMail:    simon@darkside.demon.co.uk
  FidoNet:  2:254/524.28
  AmigaNet: 39.139/1.28

