- Due to the popular demand, Elastic Reality (formerly known as ASDG) has
  been aquired as part of a merger with AVID Technology, based in Tewksbury,
  USA. From a press release by AVID Technology: 

  We still greatly value our Amiga customers and want to provide you with
  the best support that we are able but due to the afore mentioned changes,
  things will be somewhat different than they were in the past for our 
  Amiga customers. The most major chage is that we will no longer be able
  to offer telephone (voice) support to our Amiga customers. This is 
  regrettable but as we no longer maintain support of any our products at
  our Madison, WI site, this is the only way we can still offer support to
  our Amiga customers.
  The other major change is that we are no longer offering unlimited
  technical support of our Amiga products. This is being done to keep in
  line with our (and AVID's) technical support policy which provides 90 
  days of free support after purchase. This policy started (retroactively)
  on June 1, 1995 for all currently registered owners of ERI Amiga 
  products. AVID policy for support after the initial 90 days have expired
  is to purchase a one (1) year technical support extension package (this
  is subject to change for ERI Amiga products).
  ERI's Amiga products are still available for sale. Call (608)273-6585 and
  hold for the operator and let then now you are interested in purchasing
  an Amiga product.
  ERI's Amiga technical support is available via fax, mail or online 
  services.

  ERI Amiga Support
  925 Stewart St.
  Madison, WI 53713
  FAX: (608)271-1988
  EMail: erisupport@aol.com
  EMAil: 74774,1542@compuserve.com

  Thank you for your support & cooperation.
  Christopher P. Edgin
  (ERI Technical Support Manager)
  AVID Customer Service 

