- Soft-Logik is about to release a PageStream patch version 3.0h.
  This is the eighth free update patch to PageStream3. This update
  implements most of the remaining text features such as automatic
  hyphenation, paragraph spacing and page numbering. As you can tell
  from the Changes list below, this is the most important update yet
  and the program is getting much closer to complete!
  Typing speed has been improved in this version by 25% in frames with
  small amounts of text, and by 300% in frames with large amounts of
  text! Many other text speed improvements have been made, including
  improved memory handling. Text is still slower than we would like,
  but it is definitely better!
  Non-PostScript printing speed has been improved in some cases. (See
  Technical Notes for details.) Soft-Logik plans to significantly
  increase the speed of all non-PostScript black and white (Ordered
  and Halftone) printing for v3.1.
  Soft-Logik plans one more interim update (3.0i). It will finish most
  of the remaining object features including the Pen and Reshape tools.
  After 3.0i Soft-Logik will complete 3.0 and renumber it to 3.1. This
  is the long-awaited free update. v3.1 will be available online for
  approximately one month before Soft-Logik send out any free updates.
  This will give Soft-Logik a chance to ensure it's solid before sending
  out updates. If you've downloaded the patches, Soft-Logik recommends
  getting the 3.1 patch so you can get PageStream 3.1 as soon as
  possible.

  The new version 3.0h has following changes compare to version 3.0g:

  - OPENING/SAVING AND IMPORTING/EXPORTING:
    - Implemented Revert to Saved.
    - Implemented external articles and graphics. FPOs (see page 221) are
      not created yet, so bitmap pictures must still be imported in their
      entirety. File notification is not yet implemented.
    - Fixed a bug that prevented a few users from importing or opening
      some files. Symptoms included not being able to open a PageStream2
      document and not being able to import a graphic from a floppy disk.
    - Fixed canceling of graphic export which gave a recoverable alert.
    - Fixed a bug with enforcer hits with AutoSave.
    - Fixed a bug that distorted some scaled drawings in documents when
      the documents were reloaded.
    - Removed the "Line has LF" option from the ProWrite import requester
      which was not applicable to this format.
    - Fixed a problem with colors being added to the palette incorrectly
      when importing drawings.
    - Export DR2D line weight problem fixed.

  - DOCUMENT STRUCTURE:
    - Implemented page numbering. Inserting a page number variable now
      works as expected.
    - Fixed the problem with deleting a master page currently in use.
    - Fixed the enforcer hit problem with inserting pages.
    - Implemented the keyboard shortcuts for changing pages: Go to Page
      (Ctrl G), Go to Last Viewed Page (Shift Ctrl G), Previous Page
      (Ctrl J), First Page (Shift Ctrl J), Next Page (Ctrl K), and Last
      Page (Shift Ctrl K).
    - Added a verification requester for deleting pages.
    - Entering out of range values into the New Document requester will
      no longer crash PageStream.

  - TEXT AND FONTS:
    - Implemented Paragraph Spacing.
    - Implemented Auto Hyphenation.
    - Changed Auto Hyphenation to default to Off instead of On. Changed
      the default Auto Hyphenation values from 4,2,2,2,0.5" to 5,3,2,3,
      0.25" (order of options in the requester), which we think are more
      suitable defaults.
    - Implemented Insert Soft Hyphen.
    - Fixed most known insertion point (text cursor) related problems.
      The blinking cursor you see on screen will now accurately reflect
      where it really is. (If you place the cursor in a linked series of
      frames containing no text, it will appear in the last one at this
      time. Ignore this error for now.)
    - Fixed the crash problem with double/triple clicking to select.
    - Fixed auto kerning of PostScript fonts.
    - Fixed inserting of date and time variables.
    - Fixed disappearing fi, fl, oe, ae... characters in some of the
      standard fonts. Non-existant ligatures were being substituted for
      these. Updated 'fm' files that solve the problem are included with
      this version.
    - Fixed several problems with rotated text.
    - Fixed a problem with reordering and applying tabs.
    - Implemented the Manual Kern requester sample display.
    - Added a "Remove" gadget to the Manual Kern requester. This removes
      the applied manual kerning.
    - To remove manual kerning from a block of text, you no longer have
      to hold down a Shift key while choosing Manual Kern.
    - Moved the overset indicator to directly below the bottom right
      corner of overset text frames, and fixed the "hotspot" for picking
      up text frame linking.
    - Previous versions of PageStream3 required that lines of text be at
      least 0.5" long. Creating text columns narrower than this resulted
      in not being able to enter text. The reason for this 'feature' is
      to prevent bad typesetting with wordwrap. It has been changed so
      that if the minimum line length is greater than half the width of
      the column, it is ignored. This means it will still work as
      intended for text wrap, but you can now create columns as narrow as
      you want.

  - PRINTING, ALL TYPES:
    - Implemented the Print Blank Page option in Print.
    - Fixed printing of a range of pages in a chapter.
    - Fixed printing of a single chapter.
    - Fixed the display of units in the Printing Preferences requester,
      which ignored your measurement system default.
    - Fixed the distorted aspect ratio problem with bitmap pictures.
    - Fixed the distorted aspect ratio problem with landscape printing.
    - Fixed an enforcer hit problem with printing gradient fills to non-
      PostScript printers.

  - POSTSCRIPT PRINTER DRIVER:
    - If a PPD can't be loaded, it will now display an alert explaining
      why. The information provided by the alert requester should be
      reported to the printer manufacturer, because it is their error.
      Some Lexmark, Autologic and Varityper PPD files have been found to
      have basic errors.
    - Fixed the reversed vertical offset for radial fills.

  - HP PRINTER DRIVER:
    - Now remembers your default paper size.

  - FARGO PRINTER DRIVER:
    - Fixed Dye Sub Mono printing, which printed negative.

  - OBJECTS:
    - Clicking anywhere within an object's bounding box will no longer
      select it. Object selection now works as explained in the manual.
    - Fixed drawing with the Polygon tool.
    - Fixed the vertical offset and default rotation values in Transform.
    - Moving and resizing a frame now redraws the overset indicator if
      applicable.
    - Fixed an enforcer hit problem with displaying gradient fills.
    - Fixed problems with turning off text wrap.
    - Fixed the problem with pulling object size handles over the
      opposite size handles (negative resizing).

  - COLOR:
    - Fixed editing a library-based color which could default to the
      wrong color library.
    - Editing an imported color now changes it to a non-imported color.
     (The "imported" icon will no longer be shown next to it in the
     color lists.)

  - INTERFACE:
    - You can now press the Esc key to exit any requester in PageStream3
      or BME2 that has a Cancel gadget. Like pressing Return for the
      default gadget, the text cursor cannot be in a text gadget when you
      press Esc. If it is in a text gadget, press Return to exit the
      gadget and then Esc to cancel the requester.
    - Added a "Technical Support" command to the Settings menu above
      Help. This opens the online help system to the Technical Support
      Options section.
    - Fixed multiplication and division in text gadgets when using units
      other than the current measurement system.
    - Changed multiline text gadgets and non-editable text strings to
      break lines on slashes and dashes, in addition to spaces. This
      prevents unnecessary wordwrap in the Navigator's Tips gadget.
    - Corrected the text gadget tab order in the New Document and Edit
      Master Page requesters.
    - Modified the Tab and Paragraph Format requesters so that 6
      characters can be seen in the text gadgets in which you may enter
      unicode characters.
    - PageStream and BME now accept unaccented characters for keyboard
      shortcuts in requesters even if the character has an accent. For
      example, you can type "o" instead of "v". This is not of concern to
      users of the English version of PageStream3.

  - MISCELLANEOUS:
    - Fixed the fatal error that occurred when you opened a document or
      created a new one and the default view magnification was set to a
      percentage size. (Anything other than Full Page or Full Width.)
   - Fixed Cut, Copy, Paste, Erase and Undo toolbar buttons.
   - Fixed copying of objects between documents which also copied text
     style tags.
   - The Edit palette is now updated when you undo an action.
   - Margin guides for double-sided master pages now work correctly.
   - Toggling Show Rulers off no longer redraws the screen.
   - The About requester picture (splash screen) was reduced in size by
     10%, so it should display more quickly.

  - SEND TO EDITOR:
    - Fixed all send to editor scripts to work properly when quitting an
      editor and not just when closing an editor's window.
    - Fixed the spell check in PageLiner problem that returned the
      article to PageStream with no changes.
    - If PageStream3 is run from a Shell, Send to Editor will no longer
      output to the Shell that the hotlinked files have been deleted.

  - OTHER MACRO SCRIPTS:
    - "Duplicate To Page" is now an internal macro rather than an
      external script. There was no need for it to use ARexx, and it's
      faster as an internal macro.
    - New "Clear Ruler Guides" internal macro. This deletes all guides
      set with the Set Guides requester for the current master page.
    - Corrected the Open Template macro data for Avery labels size 5162.

  - MACRO RECORDING:
    - Fixed recording the insertion of unicode characters in requesters.
      An extra backslash is inserted when recording setting the bullet
      character in Paragraph Format or the fill character in Tabs so that
      these macros can be played back successfully. If the macro is
      exported, the second backslash will be removed automatically.
    - Fixed recording the playback of another macro. Instead of ignoring
      the played back macro as explained on page 341, it will now record
      the actions of the macro.

  - MACRO COMMANDS:
    - New commands: setlanguage, revertdocument.
    - Added new parameters for: setpagenumbering, getpagenumbering,
      setchapternumbering, getchapternumbering, insertnumber, insertdate,
      inserttime, insertrevision, insertsoft, sethyphenlanguage,
      deletepage.
    - GetChoice: button 1 is now the default gadget, and button 2 is the
      gadget which will be activated by the Esc key.
    - AddARexxGadget: the second exit button added will now be the gadget
      activated by the Esc key.
    - Fixed a problem with changing pages from a macro when no document
      windows were open.

  - HELP SYSTEM:
    - Made the tips accessible from the help system's main contents
      screen. Note that the tips cannot be wordwrapped in AmigaDOS 2
      AmigaGuide, so you will have to scroll the help screen horizontally
      to read each paragraph. The tips will be properly formatted if you
      have AmigaDOS 3.
    - Added a list of clip art companies to the help system. (Accessible
      from the main Contents screen.)
    - Now lists new manual errata corrections with an asterisk.
    - Corrected a few nodes that did not link to the correct sections.

  - PAGELINER:
    - Fixed a problem with using the getarticle macro command during spell
      checking.

  - BME:
    - Fixed a bug with the Clone feature. Cloned pictures would crash BME
      when closed.
    - Fixed the problem with the right half (or more) of a picture being
      displayed incorrectly when viewed at less than 100%. This happened
      only with less than 24 bit RGB and less than 32 bit CMYK pictures.
    - Fixed the potential crash problem with zooming in on pictures that
      were less than 24 bit RGB or less than 32 bit CMYK pictures.
    - Fixed the incorrect color problem when editing a 24 bit picture, or
      converting a picture to 24 bits.
    - Move the default path options from the Settings/General command to
      the new Settings/Paths command to make BME more like PageStream.
    - Editing a palette picture's colors now sets the picture status
      indicator.
    - Now sets the foreground and background colors correctly when you
      convert a picture to another type.
    - Can now click in the gray area outside of a picture to deselect an
      area.
    - You can now use the Backspace key to delete a selected area.
    - Improved the Sharpen and Emboss effects. They now work better than
      before at the edges of the picture.
    - Improved the speed of the Contrast and Brightness effects.

  This free upgrade patch will be available in AmiNet.

-  Soft-Logik's BitMapEditor (BME) is now available in a new version (BME2)
   . BME2 has a number of useful effects, including Pixelize, Brightness,
   Contrast, Emboss and the new Gary's Effects. This set of exciting 
   effects is plug and play simple. Just install them and twelve new menu
   commands will appear the next time you run BME! Apply these effects to
   an entire image or to a selected area. The new effects are:

   - Solarize, allows you to set the threshold above which pixels are 
     negated. The resulting effect is a combination of positive and 
     negative images
   - Median, streamlines pixel values to make colors more consistent
   - Average, similar to Median, but more suitable for some pictures
   - Minimum, spreads out dark areas and shrinks bright areas
   - Maximum, spreads out bright areas and shrinks dark areas
   - Equalize, evens out pixel values to make shadow details more apparent
   - Threshold, sets the cutoff point for conversion to black and white
   - Hue/Saturation, changes the hue and saturation of all colors at once
   - Gamma, brightens the middle range of gray levels without losing
     significant detail
   - Blur, takes off sharp edges by eliminating noise
   - Histogram, graphs the distribution of color values. Use before and
     after applying other effects to see their results
   - Convolve, this offers total control and has 20 presets, including:
     - Gaussian Blur: to add haze;
     - Gaussian Sharpen: to remove haze;
     - Laplacian Edge Enhancement: to highlight edges and darken other 
       areas;
     - Low-Pass: to enhance dark areas;
     - High-Pass: to emphasize bright areas;
     - Vertical Smooth: to smooth NTSC video images
   
  These are only a few of the presets. You can also load and save your own,
  and control all of the effects with ARexx.
  These effects are easy to use and fun to experiment with. Try an effect
  with its default settings, and if you don't like the results, simply
  choose Undo, change the effect's slider gadget, and try it again. If you
  use pictures in PageStream3, you need Gary's Effects to give your
  pictures the right look. 

  Gary's Effects is available now from Soft-Logik for $25 US.

