- A new bug fixed version 5.11 of DirectoryOpus is now released. This new
  version is free of charge to all current DOpus 5.0/5.1 users.
  Also a German update is available as well. Free catalog files for other
  languages will be posted to AmiNet as they become available.
  The new version 5.11 has these additional features:

  - Ability to play soundtracker modules to the PLAY command. DOpus 5.11
    supports most popular soundtracker formats
  - A BEEP command has been included in the internal commands. This simply
    makes a "beep"  sound to  notify you,  for example,  when a sequence of
    commands have finished
  - The  Directory  Opus screen can now be made the Default Public screen.
    A new toggle menu has been added to the Settings Menu
  - Programs which do not open their own screen will generally use the
    default public screen when opening windows. For example, with Dopus as
    the default pubscreen, most workbench programs, the Shell, Clock  and
    other utilities will now open on the Dopus Screen
  - The DeviceList command has been expanded with addition of the FULL
    parameter switch. This will expand  the Assign list to show the full
    path of single and any multiple-directory assignments  in the system.
    If not specified, the device list  will be  in the old format.
  - More Drag and Drop functionality:
    - The Selection Destination requester is now an AppWindow. You can now
      drag  & drop a destination drive onto the window to set the path
    - You can now drag and drop within Function Editors; either to swap
      function lines around within the one editor or to copy function lines
      to another editor. If you hold down shift while you drag a function
      line from one editor to another, the entire function will be copied
    - You can now drop files on Program Group icons to  add them to the
      group. Before you had to actually open the group to add new entries
    - You can now change item  positions  within  the menu Editors using
      drag and  drop. (instead  of  with  the Move Up/Down buttons)
  - Non-DOS disk icons are now shown (like in Workbench); a new option
    (Environment/Display  Options/Hide  bad  disks) allows you to hide
    these icons again if you wish to unclutter your backdrop window.
  - Added "Skip All" button to Copyfunction. Now, if a file exists you
    now get the option to skip all, meaning ALL files that already exist
    will be skipped
  - Added Lister Options to Environment configuration. You can now turn the
    device list off in new listers, change the behaviour of a double right
    button click to  bring  up  the  Format  Editor  in a lister, and can 
    set the default size of new listers
  - Added popup  menu to custom Button Bank window (right mouse button
    over button window title bar), with Iconify feature
  - A lot of AREXX changes and enhancements
  - and a lot of minor changes and bug fixes

  GPSoftware
  PO Box 570 Ashgrove,
  Qld Australia 4060
  Australia
  Phone/Fax: +61 7 3661402
  EMail: zzgperry@mailbox.uq.oz.au

