- Petter Nilsen's multi-format offline reader THOR is now available in a
  new version 2.01. THOR 2.01 is an advanced multi-format offline reader,
  supporting the QWK, Fido, UUCP, SOUP, Bluewave, Omen, ABBS, MBBS and
  Hippo (BBBS) message formats. THOR features: 
  
  - Flexible message database system with true history, message marking,
    searching and threading. In 2.0, this database has been expanded to
    allow all sorts of messages (NetNews, Fido, ...). Xpk packing is also
    supported directly
  - Copyback and write-through file buffering system
  - Internal editor with ARexx and macro recording support
  - Extensive ARexx support with the main THOR ARexx port, the bbsread
    command host library and the FSE internal editor (a total of 121 
    commands). The bbsread command host library can be used to access all
    databases without THOR running. Many useful and powerful ARexx scripts
    are included
  - Everything can be controlled from the keyboard
  - All events (messages you write, etc.) can be edited freely after having
    been entered
  - Advanced purging system with Global settings for days and/or number of
    messages to keep. Each conference can also have separate settings
  - User name database with a fast look-up table of names that has improved
    in 2.0 by providing an editor
  - File database
  - Kill/Emphasize database with advanced support for all message fields 
    and several "haze"-levels. Wildcards are fully supported
  - Locale support
  - Support for 15 international character sets
  - Supports new 3.0 features (newlook menus, memory pools, interleaved
    screens, 24 bit palette, screen and window pictures, ....)
  - Font sensitive and Style Guide compliant user interface with a listview
    that support true ANSI colors, multi- and dragselection of enties
  - MIME compliant (UUCP and SOUP)
  - Advanced and flexible forward string, tagfile and signature system
  - It is possible to edit data, edit text, freeze and activate events
  - All search functions can take standard AmigaDOS wildcards
  - Optional reflow of message text imported into the editor
  - Search read mode implemented. It is now possible to read 

  The new version 2.01 has the following improvments:

  - Added support for the UUCP, SOUP, Fido (including multiple nets), Blue-
    wave and Omen formats
  - The user database expanded and a user editor is added
  - File database
  - Kill/Emphasize database with advanced support for all message fields 
    and several "haze"-levels. Wildcards are fully supported
  - Locale support
  - The ARexx support has been expanded further by providing a command host
    library and 50+ new commands. Many new and useful ARexx scripts are 
    included
  - Support for Xpk packing of the message base
  - Support for many new international character sets
  - Background window and screen picture can be configured
  - Support for forward string, file- and command signatures
  - All search functions can take standard AmigaDOS wildcards
  - Optional reflow of message text imported into the editor
  - Search read mode implemented. It is now possible to read
  - a lot more :-)

  The shareware version of THOR is available in AmiNet

  Ultima Thule Software
