- Alexander Stirmlinger is currently developing a new DSP-plug in card for
  the Amiga (Zorro II). The package will include DSP-application-software
  like real-time audio applications, audio harddisk-recording/editing 
  software, DSP modem emulation etc. The DSP, TI-DSP TMS320C30, that they
  are using has the following specifications:
 
  32-bit barrel shifter
  8 extended-precision registers (accumulators)
  2 address generators with 8 aux registers
  On-chip DMA
  Integer, floating point and logical operations
  Parallel alu, upto 11 commands at the same time
  Auto increment/decrement addressing
  2 32-bit timers
  32-bit data-bus, 24-bit address-bus
  40 MFLOPS
  20 MIPS
  220 MOPS
  On-chip RAM 2K * 32

  Alexander Stirmlinger
  Weinbergweg 10
  D-74831 Gundelsheim
  Germany
  
  EMail: alex@picard.unterland.de
  Fido:  2:246/1545.11@fidonet

