  There were a number of bugs present in the shareware version. Fourth 
  Level Developments and Michiel Pelt worked together to identify and
  eradicated all known bugs and to introduce new features. The filing 
  system that has produce Ami-FileSafe Version 1.0 which was subjected to
  exhaustive beta testing which confirmed that we had a stable platform for
  further development. Fourth Level Developments added a significant number
  of features which would make Ami-FileSafe operate reliably in all
  environments and provide the basis for a new filing system which is
  capable of becoming a de facto standard for the amiga and this resulted 
  in version 2.1 of Ami-FileSafe. The new version features:

  - Notification
  - Hard and soft links
  - Large disk drives
  - Auto-Booting
  - Add Buffers
  - Sophisticated Cache Routines
  - Max transfer and DMA masking
  - Very Large Directory Support
  - Setowner
  - New FreeBlock Management System
  - International Support 
  - Multi-User Filing System support

  Ami-FileSafe is to be supported in Dave Haynie`s latest version of
  DiskSalv. The next scheduled release is Version 2.2 which will include
  comprehensive file undelete features (release date August 1995) and
  will be available to all registered users free of charge.

