- State of the art text editing package GoldEd is now available in a new
  version 3.0.5. The new version features following improvements:

  - Syntax highlighting interface; 68040 recommended (3.0.0)
  - Syntax parser example libraries (3.0.0)
  - New ARexx commands/options: INDEX/S, SYNTAX, BENCH/S, BLOCK/S, PARSER,
    SYNTAX, LEVEL
  - Absolute line numbers are passed to scan handlers (3.0.0)
  - New find/functions submenu: <pattern...> (3.0.0)
  - New menu "config/syntax..." (3.0.0)
  - FuncRef window: sorting may be turned off (3.0.0)
  - Text insertion (e.g. date) faster (3.0.0)
  - Tab and backtab faster (3.0.0)
  - New API_REFRESH_MARKER refresh mode (3.0.0): API client Mirror faster
  - QuickStarter and GoldED support AREXX/K argument to select/set a port
    name (3.0.0)
  - Line insertion/removal faster (3.0.0)
  - Printer setup: option to have FF sent after last page (3.0.0)
  - Fold marker position within line adjustable (3.0.5)
  - Menu shortcuts failed to work if MENU LOAD has been used within ARexx
    macros (3.0.0)
  - The quicktarter now returns immediately if the STICKY option is not 
    used (3.0.0)
  - Paste failed if <config/exclude cursor> has been enabled during cut/
    copy of a single line (3.0.0)
  - ASCII menu converter didn't handle barlabel text (3.0.0)
  - File hunter: symbolic file names resolved at run time (3.0.0)
  - Right-to-left input removed from the editor and implemented as API
    client (3.0.0)
  - FastScroll disabled during macro playback (3.0.0)
  - Less cursor flicker during command execution (3.0.0)
  - Absolute numbers are printed if line numbers are requested (3.0.0)
  - Editor didn't remove trailing spaces during clipboard paste (3.0.1)
  - IDCMP_VANILLAKEY events are ignored if RCommand qualifier is set 
    (3.0.2)
  - Scrolling used to overwrite bottom slider if lines did equal window
    height (3.0.2)
  - OPEN RAW/S didn't work (3.0.3)
  - GUIDE SAVE acted as GUI LOAD and vice versa (3.0.4)
  - Refresh failed during syntax highlighting if scroll borders have been
    disabled (3.0.4)
  - Startup problem on pre-OS3-machines has been fixed (3.0.4)
  - REQUEST STAY uses buffer to ensure permanent display (3.0.5)
  - Catalogs are installed into the GoldED: drawer (3.0.5)

  Dietmar Eilert
  Mies-v-d-Rohe-Str.31
  52074 Aachen
  Germany

  EMail: dietmar@tomate.tng.oche.de
  Phone: +49-(0)241-81665-(pause)-22
