- Wolf Faust announces the availablity of a new version 2.07 of the higly
  professional, Studio, Printing Software. The new version features:

  - Minor enhancement to the installation script
  - Minor enhancement to the report program
  - Studio Gadgets are now ghosted at all places when an error requesters
    appear
  - New Mitsubishi monitor CIE data added
  - Canon BJC600e output module added
  - CanonBJ-EC driver now supports 600e print modes
  - MAJOR speed improvements (2-3 times faster) in the Studio printing 
    program:
      - All dither routines are written in assembler (driver routines have
        always been in assembler)
      - Canon and Epson ESC/P2 output module now supports double buffering
        with async. IO
      - optimized printing with Workbench module if image doesn't cover
        complete page
  - IFF DEEP images sometimes didn't load correctly, fixed
  - Gamma correction of monitor values were done after clipping/histogram.
    This resulted in a too dark output with clipping/histogram and CMS 
    enabled, fixed
  - Sierra3 and Sierra2 dither routines were swaped, fixed
  - A fault made it into the Stucki color binary dither routine, fixed
  - Canon BJC 70, BJ 30, BJ 200ex Extended mode Workbench driver added
  - Studio Extended Emulation output module added for BJC70, BJ 30 and
    BJ 200ex
  - Canon BJC 70 CMS profiles added
  - 600x600dpi mode added to DeskDriver/DeskDriver4C
  - Laserjet 5P/5MP support added to LaserDriver/SetupPJL
  - Defining custom pages sizes for CanonBJ5-230 and CanonBJ-EC changed

