- A new version 1.11 of Analay is now released. Analay is a new analysis
  program which provides all the standard functions such a program needs.
  The special feature of this program is the integrated DTP mode which
  allows you to layout a page with full WYSIWYG! The program is divided
  into two independent parts running at the same time as separate tasks.
  The Math Mode contains all functions for plotting and analyzing function
  graphs. It's no problem to create the derivative of functions or to 
  calculate the zeros or the area between functions to name only three of
  the many facilities. Moreover, the design of the graphs can be changed
  in many ways. You also can place texts, points, etc. in the windows or
  hatch an area. Tables, lists and legends can be created as well.
  The Layout Mode contains a small, but complete DTP program with full
  WYSIWYG and Intellifont support! It allows you to layout a page with
  function graphs, tables, lists, legends, text blocks, etc. Moreover, it
  knows formulas which no program apart form TeX was able to display or
  print up to know! The page can be printed in the highest resolution your
  Workbench printer driver allows for your printer!

  The new version 1.1 features:
  - English program texts and English documentation
  - Zoom up to 500% in Layout Mode
  - Some bug fixes
  - Fixed a bug with power functions in V1.1

  Demo version of this powerful program is available in AmiNet.

