- A new version 2.6.2 of PGP is now released. US citizens & permanent 
  residents (Green Card holders) who are WITHIN the US, may download the 
  Amiga version of PGP 2.6.2 from MIT (and elsewhere):
	telnet to net-dist.mit.edu
	log in as 'getpgp' and answer the questions (in which you state that you
  are a US citizen/permanent resident and that you promise not to 
  redistribute PGP illegally)
	telnet to net-dist.mit.edu and change to the directory given
	in your previous telnet session. (You have only a few minutes before the
  directory disappears and you'll have to start over.) or if you are a WWW
  user, follow the directions at the following URL:
	http://web.mit.edu/network/pgp-form.html
  Others should check the util/crypt directory of NON-US Aminet sites for
  PGP 2.6i, the "international" version that doesn't use RSAREF.

