- ImageLab Technology has just released the first release of Image Vision
  the long awaited and all new multimedia program for the Amiga.
  Image Vision is a new and very exciting multimedia development platform.
  It will give you the ability to create a powerful interactive 
  presentation with ease. A lot of work has been put into the user
  interface to make it simple and intuitive. Being built from modules,
  Image Vision is also very flexible. Any new feature that comes along can
  be installed without any changes to the main program.
  After using several different MultiMedia tools for a while, programmers
  at ImageLab Technology felt that none of these tools were flexible enough
  to provide with an environment that would stay "fresh". Therefore they
  decided to create an environment that was able to meet the demands the
  fast developing Information Technology have on software today. It ended
  up to be Image Vision. Many different aspects have been taken into 
  account to give the Image Vision environment the flexibility that the
  user want. A lot of work has been put into the design and performance of
  Image Vision. The interface is very easy to use and many different input
  possibilites are supported. Every function the environment provides can
  be accessed through icons, which makes working with Image Vision very
  intuitive. There is an online help system available at all times to make
  the amount of time spent with the manual minimal. Image Vision has been
  coded around an API that will allow porting to other platforms. This 
  makes Image Vision very versatile as you are not limited to one single
  platform, and the projects you create can be exported to the supported
  platforms without any conversions whatsoever. The modularity of Image 
  Vision makes it possible to configure the environment in a large number
  of ways, giving it that personal touch. New features can be added and old
  can be removed at will. Third part developers are able to make modules so
  that Image Vision supports certain specific products. Image Vision is
  totally multitasking. You may run other programs in the background, or 
  you may run Image Vision in the background. Image Vision is designed to
  provide a carefree, multithread, and multitasking environment, which is
  guaranteed to be flawless. To make the runtime part of Image Vision as
  effective as possible even the runtime processes are multitasking.
  Currently four processes are giving you the maximum performance. As you
  can see, Image Vision is truly a multitasking environemnt in more ways
  than one. It can be made general to support many different setups, or it
  can be made to support only a specific setup. The options are only 
  limited by the user, and not by the development of the Information 
  Technology. The first version of Image Vision features:

  - Easy to use drag'n'drop interface
  - Draw and manipulate your own graphical objects with the drawing tools
  - A comprehensive and intelligent online documentation that is accessible
    at all times
  - A fully working multithread multitasking environment
  - Total modularity that will make upgrades very easy and inexpensive

  A prerelease demo version is available at no charge.

  ImageLab Technology
  Box 177
  S-37122 Karlskrona
  Sweden
  Phone: +46-455-20038
  Fax:   +46-455-18866

