- DFA - DFAddress the ultimate and beautiful address utility for the Amiga
  is now available in a new version 2.237. This highly recommended Amiga 
  only program features:

  - OS2.0 "Look and Feel"
  - Locale support (Workbench 2.1 and better needed)
  - OS3.0 is supported, if available
  - Commodity support, i.e. DFA can be reached by hotkey or the Exchange
    utility of the Workbench
  - All operations in DFA are accessable via keyboard
  - The AREXX interface contains more than 30 commands
  - All windows of DFA are font sensitive
  - The DFA-Editor main window is font sensitive and resizable
  - The DFA-Editor main window is an application window
  - The program has been split into the editor, server and preferences by
    this the available memory is optimally used and DFA needs little memory
  - Program parts used by more than one part of DFA have been exported to
    shared library, the dfa.library
  - Button row, which contains the most important functions
  - Support of external files
  - Up to three EMail addresses per entry
  - Dial function (supports OwnDevUnit) recognizes BUSY, NO DIALTONE
  - The addresses can be separated into groups
  - The groups can be named (incl. shortcut)
  - New fields state and c/o
  - Network support
  - Application icon (can be toggled)
  - It is possible to use DFA as default tool
  - New "magic" icons (8 colors) by Martin Huttenloher
  - Icon generation for the address files can be switched off
  - The auto save feature can be configured
  - The format of the address listview can be changed
  - The display part in the main window of the DFA-Editor can be configured
  - Addresses can be sorted by any field of the address
  - The fonts for the DFA-Editor and the DFA-Preferences can be changed
  - The utility NewEdit is supported
  - The usage of memory pools decreases memory fragmentation
  - The load and save routines are VERY fast

  News in the new version are several bug fixes and implementation of the
  new QuickSearch function. As soon as you hit RSHIFT-<letter>, in the 
  DFAEditor main window, the first entry beginning with <letter> is 
  selected.

  Being a SAGE release, the program may be downloded from AmiNet.

