- BackMan, backup software for the Amiga, version 1.0 is finaly released.
  This all new and powerful backup software features:

  - A very user-friendly MUI (MagicUserInterface) GUI which makes use of
    this program a lovable task
  - Support for muFS (Multi User File System)
  - Support for XPK (eXternal PacKing libraries) for data compression and
    encryption, to save space and add security to your backups
  - Support for almost all the backup medium (floppy disks, tape, 
    removables, AmigaDOS files, Optical Media, etc.) and alternative
    devices (diskspare.device, mfm.device, etc.).
  - Constant support by the programmers
  - Usual backup software's features like file selection filters,
    incremental backups, etc

  A demo version is available in AmiNet.

- Interworks is shipping I-Net 225 version 1.0. I-Net 225 is a full 
  professional implimentation of, SANA-II compliant, TCP/IP for the
  Amiga and will support all systems with 802.3 compliant TCP/IP 
  network protocol stacks. This includes UNIX, SGI, MAC, PC's and
  Amigas, to name a few. TCP/IP is an internationally accepted network
  protocol which exists on virtually all computer platforms.  This gives
  different systems a common means by which to exchange data. Amiga can
  communicate with everyone else! (i.e. Mac, PC, SGI, WindowsNT etc.)
  Utilities which were written for AS225R2, should be fully compatible with
  I-Net 225.  There are quite a number of these utilities available on 
  BBS's and FTP sites around the world.
  I-Net 225 comes with a full host of clients and servers allowing the 
  Amiga to not only connect with remote hosts, but also be a host to other
  systems on the network.
  I-Net 225 is SANA-II compliant, allowing it to operate concurrently with
  any other SANA-II compliant networking package, like ENLAN-DFS.

  - Clients:
    arp, chmod, finger, ftp, host, ifconfig, last, login, lpr, ls, netstat,
    nfsc, nfsmgr, passwd, ping, rcp, rsh, rlogin, showmount, telnet,
    traceroute, whois

  - Servers:
    fingerd, ftpd, inetd, lpd, portmapd, rshd, syslogd, telnetd, timed,
    wprintd

  I-Net 225 also comes with a full set of Internet utilities:

  - GMail        - an intuition based mail reader
  - GRN          - a news reader
  - SMTP & SMTPd - mail protocol and daemon

  I-Net 225 comes with NFS Client support, allowing the Amiga to `mount'
  remote systems' devices, and have them appear as local resources.  

  The syste requires:
  - AmigaDOS version 2.04 or higher
  - SANA-II device (e.g. Ethernet, ARCNet, SLIP, PPP, etc.)
  - 1MB RAM and Hard Disk recommended

  Priced at $349.00 US, I-Net 225 comes with a 5 node license. Additional
  licenses avaiable to support over 50,000 systems! Site licenses are
  available.

  Interworks
  Professional Network Solutions
  43191 Camino Casillas
