- Jeff Shepherd announces the immediate relase of the Amiga port of Pine
  (tm) version 3.91. Pine is an integrated mail/news client for UNIX and
  now the Amiga. With Pine you can read your mail either locally or
  remotely with little work. Pine comes with a built-in editor for 
  composing email or news replies or you can use your personal editor.
  Pine has the ability of placing attachments to your email using MIME
  and spawning external viewers to view attachments you have received.
  Pine can use SMTP to post your message or use another mailer if you
  desire.  Pine has a wide variety of options and has built-in help for
  all the supplied functions and options. Pine is the best software 
  packages to use with smtp/nntp (like Elm and Grn). 
  Pine will be freeware and will need AmiTCP in order to work. Since this
  is a UNIX port, 2M is probably the minimum you will need for Pine to 
  work. Once released, Pine is downloadable from Aminet.

  Jeff Shepherd
  EMail: jsshephe@undergrad.math.uwaterloo.ca
  World Wide Web Pages: 
  http://www.undergrad.math.uwaterloo.ca/~jsshephe/index.html

