- Ralph Schmidt annouces the release of CyberGuard mainly for the 
  Cyberstorm 060. Cyberguard has the same functionality as Enforcer
  V37 (by M.Sinz) with the enhancements of a build in a disassembler
  and a GuardianAngel mode. GuardianAngel mode means that it can 
  writeprotect free memory pages to detect random write bugs that are
  rather difficult to find.
  So programmers won't miss their most used debug tool, Enforcer, when they
  develop 68060 applications. CyberGuard is uploaded to AmiNet.

