- A Linux/68k X-driver for the DMI Resolver graphics board is currently
  under development. DMI Resolver is a graphicsboard based on the TMS
  34010 processor. Unlike most of the new graphicsboards DMI board has a
  real-processor on the graphicsboard, that has its own addressspace etc.
  The board carries both DRAM (for code) and VRAM (for the display).
  The board can do upto 2048 x 2048 in 256 colors if you got enough VRAM
  installed.

