  Include $5.00 for domestic update shipping; $10.00 for international
  update shipping.  Colorado residents must include sales tax.

  ProVector version 3.0 features among others:
  - OS 2.04+ only but will take advantage of WB2.1 and WB3 features
  - AGA support
  - Good looking, easy to use, and much improved 3D user-interface with
    2.04+ look and feel
  - Using the ASL standard requesters and other standard bits
  - Improved tool control
  - Gradient fills
  - Object shearing & warping
  - Object blending (morphing from one object to another)
  - Improved text support
  - LightWave file exporting
  - Export Adobe Illustrator (all versions)
  - StylusTrace, a dedicated high quality auto-tracing program (converts
    bitmapped images into structured drawings) much better (faster, more
    accurate, more features) than the autotracing used by other programs
    on Mac/Amiga/IBM/Unix.
  - Extensive online help system using standard AmigaGuide
  - Support for all knwon Amiga graphic boards/accelerators
  - Stylus has worked close with SOFT-LOGIK to make the all new ProVector
    a good completation for PageStream 3.0, the king of DTP programs.

  for newcommers to vector based drawing softwares and ProVector, version
  2.1 of this excellent program features:

  - ProVector has a very complete and exellent Arexx interface and is fully
    programmable and extendable through Arexx As complete as you could want.
    You can do anything via ARexx that you can via the interface, and more.
    You can manipulate ProVector's internal data structures fairly directly
    , create your own custom object types (a physicist customer has created
    Feynman diagram objects, for example), create your own custom object 
    operations, etc. This in one of the most configurable Amiga software,
    since it has a very full featured ARexx implementation for user 
    customization and communication with other programs. The package 
    includes many useful ready-made ARexx macros.
  - ProVector comes with 2 HP-GL driver which can be and has been used to
    drive various sign cutting engines (vinyl cutting) like most Roland
    plotter. The IFF-DR2D format is directly supported by many curring 
    devices like Sign Engine. In addition to the tiling HP-GL driver, 
    another feature of ProVector that sign-cutters have found very useful
    is the floating point math version of ProVector. Tiling of large pages
    to multiple output pages allows you to make VERY large signs, page
    sizes, like 15 miles x 15 miles :-)
  - The input/output formats are Encapsulated PostScript (true PostScript
    editing), EPS (Encapsulated PostScript) created on all the personal and
    workstation computer platforms, IFF-ILBM (including 24-bit, ANTI-
    ALIASED ILBM), HP-GL, Illustrator/EPSF, Multiple Layers support for
    IFF-DR2D (Amiga standard format for structured drawing developed openly
    and in cooperation with the Amiga community by Stylus). It can also 
    print to any Preferences-supported printer.
    The postscript handling in ProVector is remarkable. It can save PS or
    EPS to PAR: SER: or a file.
    ProVector can be used for drawings to include in LaTeX documents and it
    works great. Specially because it provides the drawing with a correct
    BoundingBox (one that adjusts to the drawing) so dvips can position the
    figure correctly.
    That kind of data import capability is really useful when integrating
    the Amiga into today's work environment, an environment filled with a
    variety of computers running a wide spectrum of software.
  - Very fast freehand drawing tool
  - Very flexible spline tool
  - Other tools for boxes, ovals, polygonal shapes, fill control, line 
    control, text, etc.
  - Multiple projects open on-screen at one time. Multiple drawings are 
    open in separate windows and cut and paste between them is supported
  - Cut-and-paste to the Amiga clipboard
  - 255-level Undo
  - One of the fastest Amiga program, optimized for speed even on slower 
    Amigas. It uses less memory than any other vectorbased graphic package.
  - Text effects
  - Three version of the program for integer, floating point and 68020
    and up processors)
  - ProVector uses amiga multitasking enviroment very effectively. For
    example, when redrawing a screen you can go ahead and select your next
    operation and the redrawing will be aborted.
  - It supports 8 bit (256 color) per drawing out of 16 million colors via
    dithering. You can create custom fill patterns from any object.
  - It can rotate objets, text and also will "flow" text around any 
    outline. You can rotate about any point you desire, as well as rotate
    with clone, rotate by fixed increment, etc.
  - It has Splines curves Bezier cubic splines. It also can interpolate
    curves from a polygon.  It also supports elliptical arcs.
  - ProVector comes with a utility to convert PostScript Type 1 fonts to
    ProVector format, so you have quite a variety of fonts to choose from.

  AmyNews sidenote:
  We work with ProVector as well as many other structured drawing programs
  for many different platforms and we wish to mention that ProVector,
  assumimg that you can use it's exellent Arexx interface, is the fastest
  and most powerful structured drawing programs on any platfrom. We would
  like to rate the softwares that we use as follows:

  - ProVector, Amiga
  - Aldus Freehand, Mac
  - Adobe Illustrator, PC
  - Corel Draw, PC
  - MicroGraphx Designer, PC
  - Art Expression, Amiga

  If you need something for your technical drawings, something that can
  deal with EPS clipart created on any platform, something that will let
  you create your own using sophisticated structured drawing tools,
  something that will work with your other programs like Pagestream and
  FinalWriter, and that is actively supported and developed for the Amiga,
  you ought to look at ProVector. 
  Stylus has been selling and supporting ProVector for years and is 
  actively supporting and improving this software, and provids an excellent
  solution to people who need to work with structured drawing for things
  like video graphics, desktop publishing, technical drawings, and sign
  making.

