- A new version 1.5 of the awesome all new swedish text editor FrexxEd is
  released. Version 1.5 features:
  - Danish users are now able to register in Denmark using danish currency
  - Rexx/ShowFPL.rx by Edd Dumbill is an *EXCELLENT* tool for all of you
    out there, who are not quite certain of which FPL programs to execute
    and which you shouldn't execute at startup. Try it!
  - Visible is appended to the top of the default file to make executions
    of it look much better after FrexxEd is started.
  - MenuSelect is a new exception that occurs when a menu item is 
    selected.
  - New functions: "GetFileList()" , "MenuRead()" and "MenuDelete()"
  - The execute file requester now remembers the directory.
  - Functions.guide now has the node-names without the 'node_' prefix
  - GetByte(column, line) returns the byte position of the given parameters
    or the current position. Like GetCursor() but the other way around!
  - MenuAdd() now accepts optional coordinates where to add the menu item!
  - New 3D style sliders while on screen.
  - WindowToFront() with parameter -1 makes a WindowToBack
  - ExecuteFile() now accepts a file pattern to be executed
  - The 'copywb' setting is removed, the function CloneWB() is to be used
    to copy the public screen information to the FrexxEd settings.
  - An 'R' in the status-line shows if the buffer is read-only
  - The screen will beep if you try to edit a read-only buffer
  - FlipComment.FPL is made to "Flip comments around C-lines"
  - Addition of the so far pretty simple FPL debugger 'FPLdb' to the 
    FrexxEd:bin/directory as well as an FPLdb.doc file. That file improves
    FPL debugging capabilities.
  - FrexxEd now allows buffer executions to export/cache FPL programs. That
    means you can write your FPL program in a buffer when debugging it. Re-
    executing the same buffer will make FrexxEd first flush the old program
    and then run the buffer again.
  - WordWrap.FPL is updated. It doesn't leave any trailing spaces at the
    end of lines any more. Requested by Svante Hedin.
  - Update the docs. New chapters about macros appeared and updated the
    regular expression chapter
  - New version 1.1 of the fpl.library
  - New set of FPL programs:
    - DeleteSpaceEOL.FPL:
      An entirely new beast. This scans and removes white spaces at the
      end of lines before saving them if the toggle buttons says so.
    - RememberView.FPL:
      Make FrexxEd remember the view positions when "amiga 1" is pressed.
      "amiga 2" restores the views back as they were!
    - ISpell.FPL:
      ISpell interface
    - CheckLinks.FPL:
      Amigaguide document link control
    - GotoLabel.FPL:
      Collects all assembler labels in a list and lets the user select one
      to jump to. A poor man's 'ETags'!!
  - LoadSaveProject.FPL is now updated.
  - Save As... now uses a "save-style requster".
  - SASC.FPL.README has more information.
  - ResizeView() now accepts a buffer ID parameter.
  - top_offset is a new setting (info variable). If contains the line of
    the window the current view starts at. The variable is writeable.
  - Activate() accepts a new parameter: buffer ID of the buffer that the
    new view should originate from.
  - ReplaceMatch() now accepts two new additional parameters: range and
    flags.
  - ETags.FPL and the etags archive was added. A major help tool to any
    programmer using FrexxEd.
  - Escape is now equivalent to 'q' in replace prompts. Request.
  - And all known bugs are fixed.
  The crippled SHAREWARE version may be doenloaded from AmiNet.

