  more than 500 3D models, all  present in AutoCAD DXF, 3D  Studio, 
  Wavefront .obj, Video Toaster LightWave and Impulse's Imagine PC/Amiga
  formats.  It's also got  more than 400  tileable, wrappable texture maps.
  It includes a fully indexed, cross-referenced catalog of the objects.
  The 3D-ROM is a  demonstration of the translation abilities of 
  InterChange Plus, Syndesis's system for converting between 3D file 
  formats. InterChange Plus translates between  AutoCAD DXF, 3D Studio,
  Digital Arts, Wavefront, Swivel, Sculpt, VideoScape, LightWave, Imagine,
  CAD-3D, PAGErender and Vista DEM formats. Soon to come is support for
  StereoLithography, Macromedia 3DGF, Super 3D, Alias StyleGuide, Topas,
  Softimage, Inventor and Vertigo formats. All material and hierarchy
  information is preserved as best as possible. This ISO-9660 disc is
  fully accessible from Atari, MS-DOS, Macintosh, Amiga and Unix 
  workstations.

