- Tensor Productions announces the availability of CyberScape version 2.5.
  CyberScape software is currently being used on commercial and research VR
  projects around the world. It is a cost-effective and non-intrusive 
  alternative to the more expensive and cumbersome goggle/glove VR systems.
  CyberScape uses the "projected reality" metaphor by which the person or
  subject is immersed in the virtual world through real-time video input -
  the same metaphor used in VIDEOPLACE and VIDEODESK systems by Myron 
  Krueger and Mandala (R) systems by the Vivid Group.
  CyberScape is a script-based, event-driven, multi-threaded authoring
  software that takes advantage of a physically based 2D animation system.
  For example, a complete two-team volley ball experience can be 
  constructed with only about 100 lines of code. CyberScape can be used for
  many types of applications like Interactive Music and Video Performances,
  Kinetic Scuptures and Cybernetic Arts, Interactive Learning and Training,
  Virtual Reality Constructions, Hypermedia Presentations, Interactive
  Video Games etc. CyberScape version 2.5 features:
  - Inputs:
    2 video inputs (NTSC or PAL), PowerGlove in hi-res mode, 2 mouse 
    inputs, 2 MIDI inputs, and 2 ARexx inputs.
  - Outputs:
    Serial device, Parallel device, MIDI output, ARexx output, and laser-
    disk player controls.
  - Collision Detections:
    Inter-object collisions, boundary collisions, multiple collision 
    classes.
  - Object Dynamics:
    Velocity, acceleration, damping force, gravitational force, spring
    force, constrained string force, etc.
  - Event Triggering:
    Object grab and release, scene transition, timed sequence, arithmetic
    and logic operations.
  - Graphics:
    640x400 (up to 20% overscan), 8-bit (256 colors) or HAM8 (256K colors),
    standard picture, brush, and animation files.
  - Audio:
    Standard sampled sound file, MIDI output, synthesized speech.
  - User Extensions:
    Linkable object library and interface source code included.
  New features since version 2.5:
  - Amiga AGA support
  - Real-time clock support
  - Laserdisk players support
 
  Priced at $495.00 US for AGA version and $245.00 US for non-AGA version,
  CyberScape is available directly from:
  Tensor Productions (Joseph Chung Shen)
  819 Gwyne Avenue
  Santa Barbara, CA 93111
  Phone: (805) 683-2165
 
