- A new version 1.4 of the awesome all new swedish text editor FrexxEd is
  released. Here is the features list for FrexxEd:
	- 100% recursive undo, changeable undobuffer size and on/off toggle
	- Unlimited number of buffers/blocks/macros in memory
	- Unlimited line lengths and buffer sizes
	- 100% programmable, everything can be done by a script instead of
	  Interactive
	- *very* C-like programming language (FPL)
	- Clipboard support, export to/import from any unit
	- Uses V39-style memory pools
	- v39 aware, uses V39 functions when available
	- appIcon/AppWindow support
	- window/Screen/Backdrop
	- File name extension aware icon usage
	- Supports locale library, 7 languages are supported at the moment
	- Easy macro record/edit/view/play/save/load
	- Customizeable look of any ASCII character (to i.e enable the inverse
	  CED-look or the \xxx Emacs-look or...)
	- Programmable keyassigns, make any key do anything
	- Programmable mouseactions, make any mouse action perform whatever
	  you want it to
	- Rectangular/column style block marks and block pastes
	- Programmable menustrip, make it contain whatever you please!
	- Supports XPK and PowerPacker compression/decompression and
	  encryption/decryption.
	- Startup-script that loads any file into a running editor
	- >400K documentation in amigaguide format
	- Works just as good used with gfx hardware like Retina, GVP Spectrum,
	  Piccolo, Picasso II, A2024, AGA, ECS or OCS...
	- ARexx port, capable of reading and writing ARexx variables!
	- A *LOT* of additional scripts that perform a multitude of different
	  things. From mousedragging-style blockmarking, archive-flag removal
	  when saving, center line, binary editor, snake game, incremental
	  search, interactive C indenting and word wrap to generic assembler
	  filters, bookmarks, backup, autosave and programs that easy
	  interfaces RCS...
	- Supports file comments
	- Custom keymap support
	- Optional "safe save", save with temp name and then rename
	- Easily exchangeable images for icon creations/usage
	- Binary loading/editing/saving
	- Unlimited key sequence lengths
	- Ability to clone the public screen when opened as a window on such
	- Font sensitive GUI
	- Line number mode supported, start each line with the line number
	- Ability to replace/change the workings of any internal function
	  through an advanced hooking procedure
	- Mailing list and other eletronic mail support
        o runs smoothly with virtual memory managers like VMM
        o search/replace history
	- CursorActive() controls the cursor visibility
 
	Addition to the FPL programs:
  - Doubleclick on appicon generates an exception which does a
    WindowToFront() by default.
  - Full regular expression search/replace, Emacs/UNIX style.
  - RequstWindow() supports listviews sent as string arrays from FPL
  - Smaller and faster executable
  - fpl.library v10 with lots of new features (100% ANSI C style when
    dealing with the &&, || and ?: operators, built-in sprintf() and
    more).
  - Now supports backwards replace.
  - Time controlled function invokes! Once or repeated.
  - Doubleclick on appicon moves FrexxEd to front!
  - "YankBuffer" is now viewable/editable/controllable like any other
    named block buffer.
  - KeyPress() receives the FPL program assigned to a key sequence.
  - Sort() sorts the items in a string array.
  - ReplaceMatch() performs a sort of manual replace substitution.
  - Bsearch() binary searches in a sorted string array
  - Stcgfn() and Stcgfp() returns the file or path part from a specified
    file name string.
  - and much, much more...
 
