- Hisoft of the UK is now selling "Squirrel", a SCSI2 PCMCIA interface 
  that suports up to 7 SCSI devices allowing connection of up to 7 SCSI
  devices to the Amiga at the same time. A CD-ROM, a SyQuest removable
  drive, a DAT drive, a Magneto Optical and a Tape Streamer, all on-line
  and all available at any time. The Squirrel comes complete with SCSI 
  software drivers, a host of useful SCSI programs including an audio CD
  player, a CD-to-HD sampler and easy to use SCSI drive mounting software.
  Fully tested with a wide range of SCSI & SCSI 2 peripherals, the Squirrel
  supports data transfer speeds of up to 1.3Mb/sec on a standard A1200 and 
  reaches an incredible 3Mb/sec with a 68030-accelerated A1200.
  To complement the SCSI interface HiSoft has released a number of quality
  SCSI peripherals - including double-speed & triple-speed CD-ROM drives
  and 88Mb & 270Mb SyQuest drives; these packages are shipping now at very
  competitive pricing.
  The Squirrel features 'hot' plug and unplug meaning that it is feasible
  to remove and install the interface at any time and the Squirrel software
  will automatically unmount and mount devices.
  The package comes complete with a 50-way SCSI connector cable, full
  instruction manual, warranty/registration card and easy-to-install
  software. The Squirrel SCSI is available for the Amiga A600/A1200 and is
  priced 69.95 UKP (inc VAT) + P&P.
 
- Those of you that are in need for a decent but low cost graphics tablet
  for your Amiga should take a closer look at "Tabby". It work on any 
  desired screen size and is about 4"x5" (13x10cm). The driver software is
  surprisingly goo for the lowe price of the device and is capable of
  changing the sampling methods. Different methods affect the amount of
  jitter when the stylus is between cells.
 
- The US company Quackenbush announces the release of pcmcom.device for
  the Amigas equipped with PCMCIA port. The pcmcom.device let's you use
  most PCMCIA modem and serial port cards in your PCMCIA equipped Amiga.
  The driver emulates the Amiga's 'serial.device'. Any communications 
  program that supports alternate device drivers will work with the 
  package. The driver supports the hardware FIFO buffers that are built
  into most PCMCIA modems to achieve error free communication at high 
  speeds. The driver supports connect baud rates up to 115.2 Kbps. The
  package includes a preferences program that allows extended baud rate
  selection. The software supports the X-Jack modems from Megahertz, and
  the Smart Serial Port card from Smart Modular Technologies. Most other
  PCMCIA modems and serial port cards are also supported.
  Contact Quackenbush for ordering information:
  Quackenbush
  524 Crooked Lane
  King of Prussia, PA 19406
