- German based company MAXON Computer Gmbh is currently developing a new
  version of MAXONWord, the companies very populer word processor. The
  current version features:
  - Supports endnotes/footnotes on screen in real-time WYSIWYG mode.
  - Style settings: character and paragraph attributes can be applied by 
    dragging their icon out of a list and dropping it on the paragraph/
    marked block.
  - Standard Amiga bitmap and ColourFonts
  - Compugraphic fonts supported (and all other fonts using Amiga's font
    scaling subsystem (diskfont.library >= V37), i.e. CG fonts with 
    bullet.library, others with their own "bullet.libraries".
  - Adobe Type 1 font-rasterizer (similar to Adobe Type Manager on Mac and
    Windows). Directly supports PC and NeXT Type 1 fonts, Mac fonts after
    conversion. The included fonts are in PostScript Type 1 format.
  - Support for printer build in fonts.
  - Output to maximum resolution of any printer with a Workbench driver.
    Colour printers supported too.
  - Index/Table of contents generation.
  - IFF ILBM, GIF, DR2D graphics import.
  - Each page can have an unlimited amount of text boxes, which can be
    placed in columns, rows or whatever (ala DTP). Column style boxes can
    be generated with a layout-generator.
  - Configurable menus and hotkeys.
  - Spell-checking in five languages.
 
