- Final Writer version 3.0, the powerful Amiga word processer is now
  released. Woody Williams, SoftWood's President says the new version
  makes FW easier to use. Upgrade cost for owners of Final Writer 2 will
  be the modest $5. Version 3.0 features:

  - Easy Automatic Page Numbering
    Allows you to throw a 'switch' to have page numbering done for you
    without having to do it manually in a Master Page
  - Easy Headers And Footers
    Automatically creates a master page with headers and/or footers from
    the parameters you give in a requestor. This is an extension of the
    automatic page numbering
  - Enhanced Page Number Formatting
    Allows the word 'page' and/or the section name to be included with the
    page number
  - Enhanced Text Selection
    Double-click for words, triple-click for sentences, and quadruple-click
    for paragraphs. A range of text can be selected by, while holding down
    the SHIFT key, click at the beginning position and then click again at
    the ending position; useful for selecting text spanning more than a 
    screenful of information.  When dragging to select text, how the test
    is selected depends on the number of clicks that initiated the 
    selection: double-click will select words at a time, triple-click will
    select sentences at a time, and so on
  - Drag And Drop
    Select a region of text, click and drag to another place, the selected
    text is automatically removed from its old place and inserted into the
    new place
  - Enhanced Graphics
    A Polygon tool: creates shapes with 3 or more sides. 'Special' 
    rectangle and oval tools to create shapes using bezier-like handles.
    This is a neat new feature. The 'special' rectangle tool will also
    allow you to create rounded-corner squares and rectangles
  - Type And Spell
    Checks your spelling as you type
  - More precise "snap to" grid for graphics and text blocks
  - Dictionary Hyphenation
    Adds a dictionary to the algorithm method of determining how to do
    hyphenation. It's slower because it checks the dictionary first, but
    it's more accurate
  - Auto-save Without Requestor
    You can have FW auto-save without asking your permission first
  - Selective Display Of Master Page Items
    Allows you to determine whether master page items should show on all
    pages, only on first page, or on all pages except the first page
  - Multiple Language Capability
    Supports different language spelling dictionaries and thesaureses. 
    Languages include American English, British English, German, Canadian
    French, European French, and Norwegian
 
