- The long-awaited MathScript version 1.0 is now released. MathScript is
  a formula editor, which is used to integrate mathematical formulas into
  word processors. MathScript version 1.0 features:
  - With MathScript, it is very easy to create complex formulas. To insert
    them into word processors or DTP programs they are saved as graphic 
    files. To garantee the highest possible quality they are saved as 
    vector graphics in the EPS format. They can be loaded into all word-
    processor and DTP programs which support this format (FinalWriter, 
    PageStream etc). They can be printed out by PostScript printers and
    through software PostScript interpreters on all printers.
  - Extensive amount of mathematical and physical symbols
  - Control codes for formatting (super-, subscript, fractions, roots)
  - Easy input via Workbench GUI
  - Export in the EPS format
  - ARexx port
  - support for the locale.library (beginning with OS 2.1). Available
    languages are english, german, french.
  MathScript is a shareware product priced at $15 US and is obtainable
  from:
  Simon Ihmig
  Beim Rauhen Hause 30
  22111 Hamburg
  Germany
  EMail: Ihmig@tu-harburg.d400.de
 
- ImageStudio version 1.2.1 is now released. ImageStudio is the low cost
  solution for image processing on the Amiga. The new version features:
  - Improved speed of preview redraw.
  - Added greyscale JPEG read / write.
  - Improved speed and quality of HAM6 and HAM8 file creation.
  - Improved speed and quality of 24bit internal viewer.
  - Now uses ASL screenmode requester with Workbench2.1+.
  - Added dynamic range expansion effect.
  - Now sets program stack size within the program - no need to set the
    stack from the CLI.
  - Fixed bug which caused the FlipX effect to work incorrectly with
    24bit images.
  - Fixed bug which caused non-AGA Amigas to think that they could view
    64, 128 and 256 colour pictures directly.
  - Few minor bug fixes and improvements.
 
- Douglas M. Dyer announces the realease of amiCheck, checkbook/account
  manager, version 1.31. amiCheck is doubtless, one of the best checkbook
  program for the Amiga or anyother platform. It has a very solid but
  simple to use GUI and is superbly suited for the professional Amiga
  users. amiCheck has extensive automation capabilities and can be driven
  almost entirely by keyboard if desired. The interface is font-sensitive
  and on the workbench so graphics board compatibility is high. Release 
  note for new version 1.31:
  - Interface
    - Floating palette window of templates.
    - Various GUI improvements
  - Preference menu
    - Two register styles (toggle showing memo)
    - Configure double-click action on transactions
  - Summarize multiple accounts
    - View total current or statement balances, tax deductions
    - Make project files with account lists
  - Filtering
    - Use AmigaDOS pattern matching on payee and memo fields
