- Utilities Unlimited International, inventer of the Amiga Emplant
  technology is announcing the new version 5.0 of the software for the
  Macintosh emulation module. Jim Drew of UU, showed "e586DX", the IBM-PC
  module for the Emplant at the Dec 94 Word of Amiga Show in London.
  The software emulates a Pentium chip (without the bug :-). The  CPUID
  instruction  returns  "Amiga  Inside"  as vendor information :-)
  The emulation requires a GFX board with a VGA controller, like the
  Picasso  or Piccolo. The emulation works  very stable. All x86 
  instructions are translated 1-to-1 on the fly, so the speed of the 
  emulation depends on the type of  operation. On the test machine at
  the show, memory moves were 2.5 times faster than on a 486DX2-66, but
  computational intensive instructions are slower.
  The PC emulator will be available in mid  January 95.  It will require
  a replacement of a logic chip on the Emplant board  and the emulation 
  software.
 
- Helmut Hoffmann announces the release of EGSPhotoAlbum version 1.7, the
  comfortable picture management and presentation software for EGS 
  equipped Amigas. Here is a list of improvements in version 1.7:
  - User interface
    There is now a page menu in the preview page window, which allows to
    flip the pages without use of the control window. The menu entries
    also have keyboard shortcuts.
  - Remove function
    The delete function of V1.5 has been extended by a remove function,
    which does not actually delete files on disk but just removes pictures
    from the preview page
  - Separate directory for preview files selectable
    You can now select a separate preview file directory. This allows 
    usage of the fast preview files also with readonly media as CD-ROMs
  - Different preview file formats which can save disk space
    You can now select different preview file formats to optimize speed
    or disk usage (former versions only used the fast but uncompressed
    P6 format; now IFF or JPeg can also be used for preview files).
  Helmut Hoffmann's wonderful EGS-TV is now available in a new verison 
  3.6b. EGS-TV now officially support the ImpactVision IV24 framegrabber.
  The ImpactVision IV24 users can use EGS-TV for:
  - A fascinating Blue Screen Keying effect
  - Record sequences of video directly to harddisk
  - Comfortably grab an unlimited number of single pictures, view them in
    separate windows in 24Bit quality in high speed, save them in many 
    formats (e.g. JPeg, IFF24, ...) or transfer them to other programs
 
