- Oxxi reports that the long awaited text editor TurboText TT is now
  finaly out in version 2.0! upgrade fee for the current owners is 20$.
  There are litterally hundreds of enhancements throughout the new version
  , but the main improvments are:
  - Performance has been substantially increased throughout, in virtually
    every area.
  - The ASL file, font, and screen mode requesters are now used.
  - The user-interface is now fully font-sensitive.
  - There is full on-line AmigaGuide documentation and help.
  - The program generally uses much less memory, especially with large
    documents in systems that run MungWall.
  - Each document window can now have its own menu strip, font, text color,
    keyboard bindings, etc.
  - Each document window can now be opened on separate public screens.
  - The Find and Find & Change windows now feature history in their text
    gadgets.
  - TurboText takes advantage of AmigaDOS 3.0/3.1 features, such as new look
    menus, system busy pointer, full system pen selection support,
    multi-character menu shortcut keys, and other miscellaneous items.
