- The US company FutureVideo announces the release it's all new V-Station
  3300 for the NewTek's Video Toaster. The A/B roll hardware/software
  video editor combines the power of a multitasking, multiple event editor
  with the versatility of the Video Toaster's effects, character
  generation and framestores. V-Station 3300 is capable of direct AREXX
  communication with the Toaster, allowing all of the Toaster's settings
  to be read directly back to the V-Station and saved as part of the event
  record.
  Using intuitive, point-and-click interface and armed with an online
  help system, easy-to-read software screens, and a built-in Tape
  Logging capability, video editing has never been easier.
  V-Station 3300 is compatible with various "prosumer" VCRs and camcorders
  fitted with Panasonic's Control-M or Sony's Control-L (LANC). Powerful
  options including VTR Driver Kits, SMPTE/EBU time code (LTC) readers,
  uppgradeable software and controller firmware are also available.
 
