- WordWorth version 3.1 from Digita International is out now. Upgrade fee
  from version 3.0 is £14.99. The version 3.0 of WordWorth has these
  specification:
  - DISPLAY
    - Always WYSIWYG (what you see is what you get) display from screen
      to printed page.
    - Tool bar which may be costomised from a range of large or small
      icons. Perform over 100 tasks by simply clicking an icon.
    - Human Interface Protocol(tm) v2, combines Workbench look and feel
      with the new super-intuitive HIP(tm) style.
    - Zoom magnification from 25 to 400% in 1% steps.
    - Sizes: A3, A4, A5, US standard and legal, wide tractor (132
      column), custom, facing pages.
    - Columns (1-32),with variable gutters.
    - Tableswith calculations
    - Personalised standard letters with mailing database (mail merging)
    - Margins left, right, top, bottom (optional show or hide).
    - Multi-line, mixed font, headers and footers (left and right) 
      displayed on screen.
    - User definable colours for background and text, with background 
      cocktail colour themes.
    - Switch screenmodes at any time. All Amiga resolutions supported.
    - Screen saver, clock and playtime game.
    - Comprehensive settings so that you can customise Wordworth just
      the  way you like it.
  - EDITING
    - Cut,copy, paste, erase text; drag and drop editing.
    - Copy and paste paragraph format.
    - Undo or repeat last operation.
    - Go to page, bookmark and endnote.
    - Find and replace (word, typeface, stype and special characters).
    - British English Collins spelling checker provided by Proximity
      Collins Linguibase.
    - 110,370 word dictionary with hyphenation.
    - 26,000 Merriam-Websters legal medical supplement.
    - Check word, document, or as you type.
    - Foreign language dictionaries available.
    - British Collins Thesaurus provided by Proximity Collins with 
      826,000 synonyms.
  - Digisense - built in intelligence:
    - Auto correct, corrects as you type.
    - Librarian, like a real library, lets you store text from documents
      and easily recall it at any time.
    - Table of contents and list generator.
    - Index creator.
    - Endnotes and bookmarks.
    - Speech - speak selectio, whole document, speak as you type.
    - Optional display for hidden codes like carriage return, tabs,
      spaces and special codes.
    - Full support of Commodore keypad commands (PageUp, Help, etc).
    - Swap adjacent characters.
    - Case conversion.
  - TEXT FORMATTING
    - Agfa® Intellifont® technology, which provides scalable fonts from
      3 to over 1,000 points in size.
    - Font support includes Compugraphic® outline fonts, Adobe PostScript
      fonts, TrueType® fonts, Amiga bit-mapped fonts, and Printer fonts.
    - Styles bold, italic, underline, plain, subscript, superscript.
    - Kerning (two styles), character tracking and paragraph spacing
      control.
    - Automatic and manual line spacing.
    - Alignment left, centre, right, justified.
    - TextEffects(tm), create eye-catching effects with text, colours and
      shadows, including rotation, corcle, spiral and arc.
    - Text frames.
    - Widow and orphan control.
    - Hyphenation by paragraph.
    - Text sorting.
    - Indents from left, right, first line.
    - Vertical and horizontal rulers (optional show or hide).
    - Measurements in inch, cm, mm, pica, point.
    - Tabs left, right, centre, decimal (with custom spacing character).
    - 5 Time styles (fixed orupdating).
    - 10 Date styles (fixed or updating).
    - Page numbering (5 styles), with auto count.
    - Text statistics include (for all or selected text) number of pages,
      paragraphs, lines, words, characters, pictures.
    (An Amiga fitted with atleast a 68020 processor is required to use 
    TrueType® fonts.)
  - GRAPHICS
    - Drawing tools let you freely draw lines, boxes, circles, text frames
      and TextEffects(tm) straight onto the page.
    - Lines: set line style, thickness, colour, endings, Boxes and 
      circles: set border style, thickness, fill, colour.
    - Hot link support.
    - Cut, copy, paste, erase graphics; drag and drop editing.
    - Re-sized or re-scaled on page.
    - Text auto flow left or right, vertical or contoured around image.
    - Graphic file formats supported: IFF (including HAM and Extra Half 
      Brute), PCX, BMP, GIF, TIFF, and IMG bitmapped formats. CGM, EPS
      and GEM scalable formats.
    - Fonts provided by AGFA
  - PRINTING
    - Prints text and graphics at the highest resolution of your printer.
      You can't print at any better quality.
    - Includes Digita Print Manager, worth £39,99, which maximises the 
      quality and performance of any printer by substituting special 
      Digita printer drivers.
    - Support for over 400 printers using their built-in fonts (both 
      proportional and mono-space). On-screen representation of printer's
      font to maintain WYSIWYG integrity.
    - Landscape printing.
    - Print EPS graphics with non-PostScript printers (hard disk only).
    - PostScript printer driver for standard Adobe 35 fonts, with screen
      font versions. Also rotation, oage scaling, graphics, EPS import
      and PostScript disk file creation.
    - Graphics, colour or grayscale shading.
  - DOCUMENTATION
    - Instruction book - 333 pages, with detailed tutorials, reference 
      section, typography explained and over 150 illustrations.
    - On-line Amigaguide help whenever you need, so you can learn 
      Wordworth as you use it.
    - Personal registration number - your passport to on-going technical
      support and updates.
  - FILE HANDELING
    - Open documents created in any previous version of Wordworth.
    - Easy modular auto-install for hard or floppy disk.
    - Timed auto save and backup, with reminder.
    - Revert to last saved document.
    - Open multiple documents.
    - Templates
    - Mail-merge (supports Digita Mailshot Plus, Digita Datastore, 
      Superbase, DIF, ASCII), with powerful costomisation facilities.
    - Text file formats supported: ASCII, MSWorks for Windows, MSWindows
      Write, Word for DOS, Wordstar, WordPerfect for DOS, and RTF.
  The Wordworth English language dictionary and thesaurus can be easily
  substituted with one of the following: French, Italian, German
 
