- The German based company Advanced Systems & Software, AS&S, have just
  announced a 64bit Zorro III gfx board, the CyberVision64. It is based on
  the Vision864 graphic chip by S3 and allows for a maximum of 4MB DRAM.
  Running with a pixel clock of 135 Mhz, the maximum resolution is 1280x
  1024 256 colours at 72Hz.  24bit modes are available up to a resolution
  of 800x600. It also features planar to chunky  conversion hardware which
  ought to speed up the emulation. A pass through for the Amiga signal is
  optional. It has a feature connector for add-ons such as JPEG or MPEG 
  boards. The only software included so far is a workbench emulator. The
  board was introduced at this years WOC in Cologne but will be shipping
  by the end of this year for DM 649 for 2MB Version.
  Contact AS&S at:
  Tel: (69) 5488130
  Fax: (69) 5481845
 
